<p>Companies that rank for ESG keywords capture a premium audience. Consumers willing to pay 9.7% more for sustainable products start their purchase journey with search queries like "sustainable alternatives to [product]" or "brands with ethical supply chains." B2B buyers with ESG procurement mandates search for "suppliers with carbon neutral operations" before issuing RFPs.</p>
<p>The competitive advantage is real. Products marketed as sustainable grow 2.7x faster than non-sustainable alternatives. Sustainable products hold 17% market share but account for 32% of market growth. The companies ranking for the search terms associated with that growth capture disproportionate market share.</p>
